ematic aesthetics and cultural debates, fosters film-historical knowledge, and promotes feelings of generational belonging among audiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFilm remakesxHistory and criticism. 0aFilm sequelsxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion picture audiences. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520976221?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520976221423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520976221/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles